title: For Sale:  COLT SAA 150TH ANNIVERSARY COMMERATIVE BUNTLINE IN .45 COLT WITH 10 INCH BARREL, FACTORY ENGRAVED, CASED. 1 OF 460 HANDCRAFTED LIMITED EDITION WITH THE "AM" PREFIX..
postcontent: Beautifully factory engraved Colt SAA Buntline 150TH Anniversary Limited Edition manufactured in caliber .45 Long Colt with a 10 inch barrel and high-polish blued finish. When these Colts were announced for 1986 production, Colt anticipated manufacturing 1000 examples. The Colt Archive department advised that their records indicate that Colt produced and delivered only 460 of this limited edition with “AM” (presumably for "Anniversary Model") prefixed numbers and another 30 with customer specified serial numbers and an “SA” prefix. The total production for this Anniversary edition was only 490. THIS IS NUMBER 30 in the “AM” part of the edition, and it is factory original and NEW? Celebrating 150 years of Colt craftsmanship, this Buntline revolver features floral scroll engraving with a punch dot background on the sides of the barrel and on the cylinder flats. The rear of the cylinder has a simple scroll pattern. The back strap is gold etched with a floral design along the spine. At the top of the back strap, directly behind the hammer, Colt etched in gold the sesquicentennial message "150 YEARS OF COLT CRAFTSMANSHIP" arched over the circled 150th Rampant Colt logo.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Vintage McCulloch Super Pro 125C American Musclesaw
postcontent: I have a vintage McCulloch Super Pro 125C american made musclesaw for sale or trade.  I bought the saw off of ebay a few years ago and did a complete mechanical restoration on it.  I left the outside appearance untuched in original condition because it gives the saw a history and adds character.  The saw was bought straight out of the Pacific Northwest and was used to cut giant Douglas Fir, Sugar Pine, Cedar, and Redwood trees.  The saw is complete and in perfect running condition.  The original cylinder was sent to US CHROME CO. and was Nicom/Nickasil plated and is like new. Recent compression test conducted with saw cold showed just over 140psi.  The saw also has a new piston, rings, bearings, seals, clutch & drum, sproket, airfilter, fuel filter & fuel line, ignition module, ignition coil, and lots of other NOS parts and new vibration mounts.  All New parts that were replaced were NOS or new parts that were modified to replace old parts.  The ignition was converted from points to electronic and the saw has a low use excellent condition Cannon 50" Sprocket Nose bar with new Carlton .404 pitch, .063 guage full skip, square chisel chain.  This saw is 123cc of American made muscle from the 1970's and was made for the biggest trees the Pacific Northwest had to offer.  This saw will run up to a 60" bar and is very popular with Vintage Hotsaw fans.  I have a lot of NOS parts that I will include with the saw including a NOS spare cylinder and a usable McCulloch 101 Cart cylinder if you want to hop this beast up for max power.  $800 OBO/Trade.

Using such an enhanced trigger system consolidates ease of use and safety into a convenient, innovative trigger operation—one that reduces the chance of unintended firing. And in case of an ammunition-related failure to fire, all that is needed is an additional second or third squeeze of the trigger without the need of first pulling the slide back to re-cock the pistol. The enhanced LEM trigger system combines the reliability of a double action revolver trigger with the crisp trigger of a single action pistol. P30S models have an ambidextrous safety lever mounted on both sides of the frame. S models are available in conventional double-action/single action trigger mode and with HK’s enhanced double action only Law Enforcement Modification trigger A Picatinny rail molded into the front of the frame makes mounting lights, laser aimers, or other accessories easy and convenient. title: For Sale:  Franchi SPAS-12
postcontent: The Franchi SPAS-12 is a combat shotgun manufactured by Italian firearms company Franchi from 1979 to 2000. Production stopped fully in the year 2000 in favour of the newer, enhanced version, the SPAS-15, however, production of the SPAS-15 ceased in 2005, meaning there are currently no SPAS shotguns being produced. Only five percent (about 1,850) of the estimated Franchi SPAS 12 shotguns manufactured were imported into the United States. The SPAS-12 is a dual-mode shotgun, adjustable for semi-automatic or pump-action operation. The SPAS-12 was sold to military and police users worldwide on the civilian market.
